29/01/2007
EPIRUS, Greece -- President Karolos Papoulias is calling for more respect of the rights of the Greek minority in Albania. 
In a speech Sunday (January 28th), Papoulias said the ethnic Greek community in Albania continues to struggle for its rights. 
He added that Greece is doing everything in its power to improve bilateral ties with neighbouring Albania. 
The president also reiterated Greece's full support for Albania's Euro-Atlantic integration bid. 
(Albanian News - 29/01/07; ANA-MPA - 28/01/07)
